HTML : Hyper Text Markup Language

HTML is used for designing static web pages

HTML commands are called Tags and tags are written within <TAG>
Type of HTML tags are :
--> Singular tags	These tags have only the beginning, no ending symbol
	Ex: <br>  <p>  <hr>  <marquee>

--> Paired tags		These tags have beginning and ending tag
	Ex:  <html> ...	</html>  
	     <b>  .....	</b>
 	     <body> ...	</body>

Some Tags have subtags 
<html>
  <head>
     <title>
       ......
     </title
  </head>
  <body>
     <table background="...." border="..">
       <th>
         <td> data </td
       </th>
       <tr>
         <td>
           .....
         </td>
       </tr>
     </table>
  </body>
</html>
Some Tags have attributes. Attribute values are given within "value" or 'value' or value

  <body bgcolor="yellow"> 

  </body>

-----------------------
HTML BASIC TAGS

Heading tags:
<H1>  heading 1 style  </H1>
<H2>  heading 2 style  </H2>
<H3>  heading 3 style  </H3>
<H4>  heading 4 style  </H4>
<H5>  heading 5 style  </H5>
<H6>  heading 6 style  </H6>

formatting tags
<b> bold </b>  OR  <strong>  </strong>
<i> italic </i>
<u> underline </u>
<big> big text </big>
<small> small text </small>
<sub>  subscript  </sub>
<sup>  superscript  </sup>
<font face="fontname" color="colour name" size="1-7">
   ...text...
</font>

anchor tag <a href="path&filename"> display text </a>
<marquee > scrolling text </marquee>
<hr size="value" color="colour name" width="%" align="left/right/center">  horizontal ruler
<br>  line break tag
<p>   paragraph break

Form tags : these are used to create form controls like text box, checkbox, button, etc.


<form name="var" action="server side filename" method="get/post">
  [formcontrol tags are given here]
</form>

Form control tags:
------------------
<input type="text" value="val" name="var"> 
'type' attribute values
text	 	: to display a text box
password 	: to display password box (characters given as input here will be shown as dots...)
number	 	: to display a box that will accept only numbers without decimal
decimal	 	: to display a box that will accept decimal values
button		: to create a command button (like save, cancel, yes, no)
checkbox	: to display a check box in which we can select it by putting a tickmark
radio		: to display multiple options out of which any one only can be selected
		   radio buttons must be used as a group of atleast 2 that has 'name' as same property value
date		: to display date values by showing a calender
time		: to show a time box that contains Hours minutes seconds and am/pm
color		: to show the colour palett from where user required colour can be selected
submit		: same like button but is used to submit the form data to the web server
reset		: same like button but it is used to clear & reset all values of the form controls to default

